Detailed Description

Generic wrapper that holds classes whose instances can be written to and restored from a Parcel.

Classes that can be wrapped by Parcelable should implement two functions:

 void writeToParcel(gaia::core::Parcel* dest, int32_t flags);
 static T* createFromParcelN(const gaia::core::Parcel& source);

 struct MySavedState {
     int32_t mInt;
     gaia::base::String mString;
     double mDouble;

     void writeToParcel(gaia::core::Parcel* dest, int32_t flags) {
         dest->writeInt(mInt);
         dest->writeString(mString);
         dest->writeDouble(mDouble);
     }

     static MySavedState* createFromParcelN(const gaia::core::Parcel& source) {
         MySavedState* me = new MySavedState();
         me->mInt = source.readInt();
         me->mString = source.readString();
         me->mDouble = source.readDouble();
         return me;
     }
 };

 MySavedState* state = new MySavedState();
 Demand demand;
 demand.putParcelableExtra("SAVE", Parcelable(state));

 Parcelable parcelable = demand.getParcelableExtra("SAVE");
 MySavedState* state2 = parcelable.getN<MySavedState>();

If you want to give your class a custom name when writing into parcel, please implement a static function in your class:

 static const char* PARCELABLE_NAME() {
     return "gaia::MyCurtomClassName";
 }
